author: Mimi Morley
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
---

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}) and finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Put a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil!) and leave it to get hot for a couple of mins. While the pan gets hot, remove the ends from the @courgette{1} then slice into rounds about 1cm thick.

Lay the courgette slices in the hot pan and cook them until slightly charred, ~{3-4%minutes} each side. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and then remove to a #plate{} or #bowl{}. Meanwhile, put a large #saucepan{} of water with a good pinch of salt on to boil for the @penne pasta{146%g}.

Put a drizzle of @olive oil{} in the now empty frying pan and add the onion and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, on medium heat until soft and golden, ~{6-7%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and @ras-el-hanout{1} and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Meanwhile, add the pasta to the boiling water. Cook for ~{10%minutes} then drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the now empty saucepan and drizzle with a little @oil{} to stop it sticking together.

Add the @lamb mince{200%g} to the pan with the onion. Cook, stirring, until browned, ~{5%minutes}, then stir in the @tinned chopped tomatoes{1}(finely chopped) and @beef stock powder{1}. Bring to a simmer then cook on a low heat until rich and tomatoey, ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The liquid should have also reduced by about a third.

Meanwhile, pop the @panko breadcrumbs{18%g}, half the parsley, the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} in a #small bowl{}. Stir in the @olive oil{2%tbsp} (see ingredients for amount). Stir the @creme fraiche{112.5%g}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and the remaining parsley into the drained pasta. Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Spoon a third of the sauce into an #ovenproof dish{}, then layer over half the pasta. Add the next third of sauce, then the remaining pasta. Spoon on the rest of the sauce, then layer over the courgette slices. Sprinkle on the cheesy breadcrumbs and pop under your grill until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Serve the lamb moussaka in #bowls{}. Enjoy!